 $\partial S\cap{\cal N}=\emptyset$. Moreover, suppose ${\cal N}_{p_j}\subseteq S$ for every singular point $p_j\in S\backslash\{p_{j_0}\}$.

Then, there is no singular point in $S$ different from $p_{j_0}$.
